00056 struct fld_cache *fld_cache_init(const char *name,
00057                                  int cache_size, int cache_threshold)
00058 {
00059         struct fld_cache *cache;
00060         ENTRY;
00061 
00062         LASSERT(name != NULL);
00063         LASSERT(cache_threshold < cache_size);
00064 
00065         OBD_ALLOC_PTR(cache);
00066         if (cache == NULL)
00067                 RETURN(ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM));
00068 
00069         INIT_LIST_HEAD(&cache->fci_entries_head);
00070         INIT_LIST_HEAD(&cache->fci_lru);
00071 
00072         cache->fci_cache_count = 0;
00073         rwlock_init(&cache->fci_lock);
00074 
00075         strlcpy(cache->fci_name, name,
00076                 sizeof(cache->fci_name));
00077 
00078         cache->fci_cache_size = cache_size;
00079         cache->fci_threshold = cache_threshold;
00080 
00081         /* Init fld cache info. */
00082         memset(&cache->fci_stat, 0, sizeof(cache->fci_stat));
00083 
00084         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "%s: FLD cache - Size: %d, Threshold: %d\n",
00085                cache->fci_name, cache_size, cache_threshold);
00086 
00087         RETURN(cache);
00088 }

00093 void fld_cache_fini(struct fld_cache *cache)
00094 {
00095         __u64 pct;
00096         ENTRY;
00097 
00098         LASSERT(cache != NULL);
00099         fld_cache_flush(cache);
00100 
00101         if (cache->fci_stat.fst_count > 0) {
00102                 pct = cache->fci_stat.fst_cache * 100;
00103                 do_div(pct, cache->fci_stat.fst_count);
00104         } else {
00105                 pct = 0;
00106         }
00107 
00108         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "FLD cache statistics (%s):\n", cache->fci_name);
00109         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "  Total reqs: "LPU64"\n", cache->fci_stat.fst_count);
00110         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "  Cache reqs: "LPU64"\n", cache->fci_stat.fst_cache);
00111         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "  Cache hits: "LPU64"%%\n", pct);
00112 
00113         OBD_FREE_PTR(cache);
00114 
00115         EXIT;
00116 }

00133 static void fld_fix_new_list(struct fld_cache *cache)
00134 {
00135         struct fld_cache_entry *f_curr;
00136         struct fld_cache_entry *f_next;
00137         struct lu_seq_range *c_range;
00138         struct lu_seq_range *n_range;
00139         struct list_head *head = &cache->fci_entries_head;
00140         ENTRY;
00141 
00142 restart_fixup:
00143 
00144         list_for_each_entry_safe(f_curr, f_next, head, fce_list) {
00145                 c_range = &f_curr->fce_range;
00146                 n_range = &f_next->fce_range;
00147 
00148                 LASSERT(lu_seq_range_is_sane(c_range));
00149                 if (&f_next->fce_list == head)
00150                         break;
00151 
00152                 if (c_range->lsr_flags != n_range->lsr_flags)
00153                         continue;
00154 
00155                 LASSERTF(c_range->lsr_start <= n_range->lsr_start,
00156                          "cur lsr_start "DRANGE" next lsr_start "DRANGE"\n",
00157                          PRANGE(c_range), PRANGE(n_range));
00158 
00159                 /* check merge possibility with next range */
00160                 if (c_range->lsr_end == n_range->lsr_start) {
00161                         if (c_range->lsr_index != n_range->lsr_index)
00162                                 continue;
00163                         n_range->lsr_start = c_range->lsr_start;
00164                         fld_cache_entry_delete(cache, f_curr);
00165                         continue;
00166                 }
00167 
00168                 /* check if current range overlaps with next range. */
00169                 if (n_range->lsr_start < c_range->lsr_end) {
00170                         if (c_range->lsr_index == n_range->lsr_index) {
00171                                 n_range->lsr_start = c_range->lsr_start;
00172                                 n_range->lsr_end = max(c_range->lsr_end,
00173                                                        n_range->lsr_end);
00174                                 fld_cache_entry_delete(cache, f_curr);
00175                         } else {
00176                                 if (n_range->lsr_end <= c_range->lsr_end) {
00177                                         *n_range = *c_range;
00178                                         fld_cache_entry_delete(cache, f_curr);
00179                                 } else
00180                                         n_range->lsr_start = c_range->lsr_end;
00181                         }
00182 
00183                         /* we could have overlap over next
00184                          * range too. better restart. */
00185                         goto restart_fixup;
00186                 }
00187 
00188                 /* kill duplicates */
00189                 if (c_range->lsr_start == n_range->lsr_start &&
00190                     c_range->lsr_end == n_range->lsr_end)
00191                         fld_cache_entry_delete(cache, f_curr);
00192         }
00193 
00194         EXIT;
00195 }

00200 static inline void fld_cache_entry_add(struct fld_cache *cache,
00201                                        struct fld_cache_entry *f_new,
00202                                        struct list_head *pos)
00203 {
00204         list_add(&f_new->fce_list, pos);
00205         list_add(&f_new->fce_lru, &cache->fci_lru);
00206 
00207         cache->fci_cache_count++;
00208         fld_fix_new_list(cache);
00209 }

00215 static int fld_cache_shrink(struct fld_cache *cache)
00216 {
00217         struct fld_cache_entry *flde;
00218         struct list_head *curr;
00219         int num = 0;
00220         ENTRY;
00221 
00222         LASSERT(cache != NULL);
00223 
00224         if (cache->fci_cache_count < cache->fci_cache_size)
00225                 RETURN(0);
00226 
00227         curr = cache->fci_lru.prev;
00228 
00229         while (cache->fci_cache_count + cache->fci_threshold >
00230                cache->fci_cache_size && curr != &cache->fci_lru) {
00231 
00232                 flde = list_entry(curr, struct fld_cache_entry, fce_lru);
00233                 curr = curr->prev;
00234                 fld_cache_entry_delete(cache, flde);
00235                 num++;
00236         }
00237 
00238         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "%s: FLD cache - Shrunk by "
00239                "%d entries\n", cache->fci_name, num);
00240 
00241         RETURN(0);
00242 }

00247 void fld_cache_flush(struct fld_cache *cache)
00248 {
00249         ENTRY;
00250 
00251         write_lock(&cache->fci_lock);
00252         cache->fci_cache_size = 0;
00253         fld_cache_shrink(cache);
00254         write_unlock(&cache->fci_lock);
00255 
00256         EXIT;
00257 }

00264 static void fld_cache_punch_hole(struct fld_cache *cache,
00265                                  struct fld_cache_entry *f_curr,
00266                                  struct fld_cache_entry *f_new)
00267 {
00268         const struct lu_seq_range *range = &f_new->fce_range;
00269         const u64 new_start  = range->lsr_start;
00270         const u64 new_end  = range->lsr_end;
00271         struct fld_cache_entry *fldt;
00272 
00273         ENTRY;
00274         OBD_ALLOC_GFP(fldt, sizeof *fldt, GFP_ATOMIC);
00275         if (!fldt) {
00276                 OBD_FREE_PTR(f_new);
00277                 EXIT;
00278                 /* overlap is not allowed, so dont mess up list. */
00279                 return;
00280         }
00281         /*  break f_curr RANGE into three RANGES:
00282          *        f_curr, f_new , fldt
00283          */
00284 
00285         /* f_new = *range */
00286 
00287         /* fldt */
00288         fldt->fce_range.lsr_start = new_end;
00289         fldt->fce_range.lsr_end = f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end;
00290         fldt->fce_range.lsr_index = f_curr->fce_range.lsr_index;
00291 
00292         /* f_curr */
00293         f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end = new_start;
00294 
00295         /* add these two entries to list */
00296         fld_cache_entry_add(cache, f_new, &f_curr->fce_list);
00297         fld_cache_entry_add(cache, fldt, &f_new->fce_list);
00298 
00299         /* no need to fixup */
00300         EXIT;
00301 }

00306 static void fld_cache_overlap_handle(struct fld_cache *cache,
00307                                 struct fld_cache_entry *f_curr,
00308                                 struct fld_cache_entry *f_new)
00309 {
00310         const struct lu_seq_range *range = &f_new->fce_range;
00311         const u64 new_start  = range->lsr_start;
00312         const u64 new_end  = range->lsr_end;
00313         const u32 mdt = range->lsr_index;
00314 
00315         /* this is overlap case, these case are checking overlapping with
00316          * prev range only. fixup will handle overlaping with next range. */
00317 
00318         if (f_curr->fce_range.lsr_index == mdt) {
00319                 f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start = min(f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start,
00320                                                   new_start);
00321 
00322                 f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end = max(f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end,
00323                                                 new_end);
00324 
00325                 OBD_FREE_PTR(f_new);
00326                 fld_fix_new_list(cache);
00327 
00328         } else if (new_start <= f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start &&
00329                         f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end <= new_end) {
00330                 /* case 1: new range completely overshadowed existing range.
00331                  *         e.g. whole range migrated. update fld cache entry */
00332 
00333                 f_curr->fce_range = *range;
00334                 OBD_FREE_PTR(f_new);
00335                 fld_fix_new_list(cache);
00336 
00337         } else if (f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start < new_start &&
00338                         new_end < f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end) {
00339                 /* case 2: new range fit within existing range. */
00340 
00341                 fld_cache_punch_hole(cache, f_curr, f_new);
00342 
00343         } else  if (new_end <= f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end) {
00344                 /* case 3: overlap:
00345                  *         [new_start [c_start  new_end)  c_end)
00346                  */
00347 
00348                 LASSERT(new_start <= f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start);
00349 
00350                 f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start = new_end;
00351                 fld_cache_entry_add(cache, f_new, f_curr->fce_list.prev);
00352 
00353         } else if (f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start <= new_start) {
00354                 /* case 4: overlap:
00355                  *         [c_start [new_start c_end) new_end)
00356                  */
00357 
00358                 LASSERT(f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end <= new_end);
00359 
00360                 f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end = new_start;
00361                 fld_cache_entry_add(cache, f_new, &f_curr->fce_list);
00362         } else
00363                 CERROR("NEW range ="DRANGE" curr = "DRANGE"\n",
00364                        PRANGE(range),PRANGE(&f_curr->fce_range));
00365 }

00388 int fld_cache_insert_nolock(struct fld_cache *cache,
00389                             struct fld_cache_entry *f_new)
00390 {
00391         struct fld_cache_entry *f_curr;
00392         struct fld_cache_entry *n;
00393         struct list_head *head;
00394         struct list_head *prev = NULL;
00395         const u64 new_start  = f_new->fce_range.lsr_start;
00396         const u64 new_end  = f_new->fce_range.lsr_end;
00397         __u32 new_flags  = f_new->fce_range.lsr_flags;
00398         ENTRY;
00399 
00400         /*
00401          * Duplicate entries are eliminated in insert op.
00402          * So we don't need to search new entry before starting
00403          * insertion loop.
00404          */
00405 
00406         if (!cache->fci_no_shrink)
00407                 fld_cache_shrink(cache);
00408 
00409         head = &cache->fci_entries_head;
00410 
00411         list_for_each_entry_safe(f_curr, n, head, fce_list) {
00412                 /* add list if next is end of list */
00413                 if (new_end < f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start ||
00414                    (new_end == f_curr->fce_range.lsr_start &&
00415                     new_flags != f_curr->fce_range.lsr_flags))
00416                         break;
00417 
00418                 prev = &f_curr->fce_list;
00419                 /* check if this range is to left of new range. */
00420                 if (new_start < f_curr->fce_range.lsr_end &&
00421                     new_flags == f_curr->fce_range.lsr_flags) {
00422                         fld_cache_overlap_handle(cache, f_curr, f_new);
00423                         goto out;
00424                 }
00425         }
00426 
00427         if (prev == NULL)
00428                 prev = head;
00429 
00430         CDEBUG(D_INFO, "insert range "DRANGE"\n", PRANGE(&f_new->fce_range));
00431         /* Add new entry to cache and lru list. */
00432         fld_cache_entry_add(cache, f_new, prev);
00433 out:
00434         RETURN(0);
00435 }

00437 int fld_cache_insert(struct fld_cache *cache,
00438                      const struct lu_seq_range *range)
00439 {
00440         struct fld_cache_entry  *flde;
00441         int rc;
00442 
00443         flde = fld_cache_entry_create(range);
00444         if (IS_ERR(flde))
00445                 RETURN(PTR_ERR(flde));
00446 
00447         write_lock(&cache->fci_lock);
00448         rc = fld_cache_insert_nolock(cache, flde);
00449         write_unlock(&cache->fci_lock);
00450         if (rc)
00451                 OBD_FREE_PTR(flde);
00452 
00453         RETURN(rc);
00454 }

00456 void fld_cache_delete_nolock(struct fld_cache *cache,
00457                       const struct lu_seq_range *range)
00458 {
00459         struct fld_cache_entry *flde;
00460         struct fld_cache_entry *tmp;
00461         struct list_head *head;
00462 
00463         head = &cache->fci_entries_head;
00464         list_for_each_entry_safe(flde, tmp, head, fce_list) {
00465                 /* add list if next is end of list */
00466                 if (range->lsr_start == flde->fce_range.lsr_start ||
00467                    (range->lsr_end == flde->fce_range.lsr_end &&
00468                     range->lsr_flags == flde->fce_range.lsr_flags)) {
00469                         fld_cache_entry_delete(cache, flde);
00470                         break;
00471                 }
00472         }
00473 }

00528 int fld_cache_lookup(struct fld_cache *cache,
00529                      const u64 seq, struct lu_seq_range *range)
00530 {
00531         struct fld_cache_entry *flde;
00532         struct fld_cache_entry *prev = NULL;
00533         struct list_head *head;
00534         ENTRY;
00535 
00536         read_lock(&cache->fci_lock);
00537         head = &cache->fci_entries_head;
00538 
00539         cache->fci_stat.fst_count++;
00540         list_for_each_entry(flde, head, fce_list) {
00541                 if (flde->fce_range.lsr_start > seq) {
00542                         if (prev != NULL)
00543                                 *range = prev->fce_range;
00544                         break;
00545                 }
00546 
00547                 prev = flde;
00548                 if (lu_seq_range_within(&flde->fce_range, seq)) {
00549                         *range = flde->fce_range;
00550 
00551                         cache->fci_stat.fst_cache++;
00552                         read_unlock(&cache->fci_lock);
00553                         RETURN(0);
00554                 }
00555         }
00556         read_unlock(&cache->fci_lock);
00557         RETURN(-ENOENT);
00558 }
